[{"_path":"/blog/2023/06/animated-number-counter-vanillajs-and-vue3","_dir":"06","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"en","title":"Make animated number counter with Vanilla js. +Vue3","description":"I implemented it because I needed to use a animated number counter, but when I saw my code that I implemented, I was very annoyed. Becuase my code...","createdAt":"2023-06-03 22:40","updatedAt":"2023-06-03 22:40","isPublished":true,"cover":"https://wbwsloxpaolxwerwiupa.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-asset/images/7befa050-553a-4ae0-a8dd-88367007c0fb.webp","tags":["Javascript","Vue","Snippet"],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I implemented it because I needed to use a animated number counter, but when I saw my code that I implemented, I was very annoyed.\nBecuase my code didn't make sense. So I searched for code made by someone else and managed to find code that satisfies the requirements that "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"can be duration-specified and can display commas every 3 digits"}]},{"type":"text","value":", and leave a record."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"code"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Code"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"v-iframe","props":{"src":"https://stackblitz.com/edit/js-vl7vcq?ctl=1&embed=1&file=index.js"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"how-it-works"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How it works"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To put it really simply, the counter we created increases in numbers at the same rate from start to finish,\nso we just have to calculate the number increased by the elapsed time and repeat it over and over again until we finish."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To explain it in more detail, if you multiply "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timeLapseRate"}]},{"type":"text","value":", which is the ratio of "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"elapsed"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"duration"}]},{"type":"text","value":", by "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"range"}]},{"type":"text","value":"(range that to animate the number), and add "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"start"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (initial value), you can obtain the value that should be shown at the elapsed time.\nBy repeating these tasks by the recursive function during duration, we can get the animation effect we want."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It's hard just to say it, so let's say you make an animation that counts from 20 to 100 for 4 seconds."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"duration = 4"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"start = 20"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"range = 80"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the end of one second, "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"elapsed = 1"}]},{"type":"text","value":", so the value we see is 1/4*80+20 = 40."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After 2 seconds, it becomes 2/4*80+20 = 60."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After 3 seconds, it becomes 3/4*80+20 = 80."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After 4 seconds, 4/4*80+20 = 100."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"explanation"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Explanation"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let's look at how the operating principles described above are applied in the code."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-javascript material-theme-lighter_material-theme-ocean","code":"const duration = 1000;\n\nconst counter = (el) => {\n  const start = +el.innerText;\n  const end = +el.dataset.counter;\n\n  if (start === end) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const range = end - start;\n  let currentValue = start;\n\n  const timeStart = Date.now();\n\n  const loop = () => {\n    const elapsed = Date.now() - timeStart;\n    const timeLapseRate = Math.min(elapsed / duration, 1);      // (2)\n    const change = timeLapseRate * range;\n    currentValue = start + change;\n    el.innerText = Math.trunc(currentValue).toLocaleString();   // (3)\n    if (timeLapseRate === 1) {                                  // (1)\n      return;\n    }\n    requestAnimationFrame(loop);                                // (4)\n  };\n\n  requestAnimationFrame(loop);\n};\n","language":"javascript","meta":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":1},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-953144"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"const"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-359564"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" duration "}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-083011"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"="}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-359564"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" "}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"ct-567313"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1000"}]},{"type":"element","ta